From d6b15f97521d798df47fd45453dc77e34fb88202 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 18:04:57 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 06/14] chronium: per-profile navigator.userAgent +
 navigator.platform + HTTP UA
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Targets plan §0.2 (login persistence): the JS-exposed user agent
string and the HTTP User-Agent header now match exactly and both
follow the per-profile JSON config. This is the single most
important consistency for not getting flagged by Google's risk
engine on Gmail / Account / YouTube.

Approach: piggyback on Chromium's existing --user-agent flag rather
than adding a parallel path. At browser startup
(PreCreateThreadsImpl, after FingerprintProfile loads the JSON) we
promote the profile's 'user_agent' field into
embedder_support::kUserAgent. Chromium's own user-agent plumbing
then handles BOTH the HTTP User-Agent header (via
user_agent_utils) AND the JS navigator.userAgent value, and the
existing AppendExtraCommandLineSwitches copy of kUserAgent in
kCommonSwitchNames carries it to every child process. Zero new code
in the user-agent generation path.

navigator.platform is patched in Blink directly because the only
existing override path (Settings::GetNavigatorPlatformOverride) is
DevTools-driven and reachable only after a DOM window exists. We
add a Chronium-priority check at the top of Navigator::platform()
that reads from blink::FingerprintState. The state is populated in
RenderThreadStarted from --fingerprint-platform, which the browser
appends from the JSON 'platform' field via
AppendExtraCommandLineSwitches (same pattern as the existing WebGL
vendor/renderer propagation).

navigator.vendor is intentionally NOT spoofed: Chrome hardcodes
'Google Inc.' for legacy compat and fingerprinters expect that
constant alongside a Chrome-shaped UA. Spoofing it would create a
detectable inconsistency.

Verified end-to-end on a httpbin echo:
  profile A (Windows JSON):
    navigator.userAgent : Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) ...
    navigator.platform  : Win32
    HTTP User-Agent     : <identical to navigator.userAgent>
  profile B (Mac JSON):
    navigator.userAgent : Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_15_7) ...
    navigator.platform  : MacIntel
    HTTP User-Agent     : <identical to navigator.userAgent>

Files touched:
- chrome/common/chrome_switches.{h,cc}                 (kFingerprintPlatform)
- chrome/browser/fingerprint/fingerprint_profile.{h,cc}
                                                       (UserAgent/Platform accessors)
- chrome/browser/chrome_browser_main.cc                (promote ua into kUserAgent)
- chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc      (propagate platform switch)
- chrome/renderer/chrome_content_renderer_client.cc    (install platform on RT start)
- third_party/blink/renderer/platform/fingerprint/
    fingerprint_state.{h,cc}                           (SetPlatform/Platform)
- third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc   (override platform())
